{"accepted":[{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #562: declared status 'open'. Formalized: yes. Let $R_r(n)$ denote the $r$-uniform hypergraph Ramsey number: the minimal $m$ such that if we $2$-colour all edges of the complete $r$-uniform hypergraph on $m$ vertices then there must be some monochromatic copy of the complete $r$-uniform hypergraph on $n$ vertices.\n\nProve that, for $r\\geq 3$,\\[\\log_{r-1} R_r(n) \\asymp_r n,\\]where $\\log_{r-1}$ denotes the $(r-1)$-fold iterated logarithm. That is, does $R_r(n)$ grow like\\[2^{2^{\\cdots n}}\\]where the tower of exponentials has height $r-1$? Prize: no. Tags: graph theory, hypergraphs, ramsey theory.","id":"vf_6bcd47fb7fece16a","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Formal-Conjectures statement: Erdos562.erdos_562 https://google-deepmind.github.io/formal-conjectures/theorem/?name=Erdos562.erdos_562.","id":"vf_81f056b7f9858a84","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[],"activity_types":[],"attempt_count":0,"banked_attempt_count":0,"commits":[],"dependency_impact":"none","detail_url":"problems/562.json","draft_proposals":[],"edges":[{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_6bcd47fb7fece16a","source_root":"sha256:1faedc24f040a60a22177b456c74b969a61ce8836082297b1835797a57b4fa56","target":"erdos:562","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_81f056b7f9858a84","source_root":"sha256:1faedc24f040a60a22177b456c74b969a61ce8836082297b1835797a57b4fa56","target":"erdos:562","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Materialized typed link between accepted findings.","inferred":true,"relation":"synthesized_from","source":"vf_81f056b7f9858a84","source_root":"sha256:1faedc24f040a60a22177b456c74b969a61ce8836082297b1835797a57b4fa56","target":"vf_6bcd47fb7fece16a","trust":"signed"}],"ext